---
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="Hosting docs"
  description="Hosting guidance for serving the Thumbrella site and related services."
>
  <Section
    eyebrow="hosting docs"
    title="Keep deployment boring"
    lede="This site is static, so the hosting guidance can stay focused on artifact delivery, cache policy, and where the runtime parts of the wider system live."
  >
    <ol>
      <li>Build the site with <code>npm run build</code>.</li>
      <li>Serve the generated <code>dist</code> directory from any static host.</li>
      <li>Document the separate runtime services that the web client and media browser talk to.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>
      For the site itself, prefer simple static hosting. Keep operational detail for the actual Thumbrella services in adjacent docs rather than coupling them to the frontend deployment story.
    </p>
  </Section>
</MainLayout>